sentences:
Sentence 0:
Application of 100 microM aspterric acid (AA), a pollen growth inhibitor, with different concentrations of indole-3-acetic acid (IAA) results in the recovery of normal pollen development of Arabidopsis thaliana.

Sentence 1:
Treatment with 100 microM AA plus 5 mM IAA significantly induced the normal seed production.

Sentence 2:
Treatment with 100 microM N-1-naphthylphthalamic acid (NPA), a polar auxin transport inhibitor, did not reduce the pollen growth but inhibited seed production.

Sentence 3:
100 microM NPA plus 5 mM IAA did not induce any seed production.

Sentence 4:
The endogenous level of IAA in stems and leaves of A. thaliana treated with 100 microM AA was similar to that of the untreated control.

Sentence 5:
In contrast to AA treatment, the IAA level by the treatment with 100 microM NPA was about twice as much as that of the untreated control.

100 microM NPA plus 5 mM IAA did not induce any seed production.
